<table width="auto"  border="0" cellspacing="0" cellpadding="0"><tr><td colspan=3>House Bill/Resolution NO. <b>HB06103</b></td></tr><tr><td colspan=3>FULL TITLE : AN ACT INSTITUTIONALIZING THE UNANG YAKAP CAMPAIGN, ADOPTING THE PROTOCOL ON ESSENTIAL NEWBORN CARE</td></tr><tr><td colspan=3>ABSTRACT : Seeks to address the disturbing trend in neonatal mortality by institutionalizing the Unang Yakap campaign which advocates the Essential Intrapartum Newborn Care ( E I N C ), a concept fully supported by W H O, describes by D O H as a series of time - bound and evidence - based interventions in caring for newborn babies and their mothers and therefore has a potential to decrease newborn death by at least half.

Involves non-costly simple ways or steps to improve health care services for babies during the first critical hours; and aims to train frontline maternal and newborn healthcare practitioners and educate pregnant women of the importance of observing the Unang Yakap protocol.

</td></tr><tr><td colspan=3>PRINCIPAL AUTHOR/S : <b>ANDAYA, MARISSA</b></td></tr><tr><td colspan=3>DATE FILED : 2020-01-29</td></tr><tr><td colspan=3>SIGNIFICANCE: NATIONAL</td></tr><tr><td colspan=3><b>ACTIONS TAKEN BY THE COMMITTEE ON RULES</b></td></tr><tr><td colspan=3>REFERRAL TO THE COMMITTEE ON HEALTH ON 2020-02-04</td></tr></table>